{title: The Bedroom}
{artist: Jim Ed Brown and Helen Cornelius}
{composer: Written by Ron Muir}

[C]Two soft pillows and tangled sheets
An unmade [F]bed where no one [C]sleeps
Standing here just [G7]looking at the [C]bedroom
Laughter was the only sound
As I slipped [F]off my wedding [C]gown
Happiness was glowing in this [G7]room
Pink [C]champagne and candle light
Love was [F]special on that [C]night
These were our first [G7]memories of the [C]bedroom
Holidays would always see
The gentle [F]way that you’d [C]wake me
Sometimes we’d talk to nearly [G7]noon
Every[C]thing we ever did
Like making [F]plans and loving [C]kids
Seems they all [G7]began here in the [C]bedroom
Then [F]came those nights and quarreling days

It all starts at night again
Love hasn’t left this lonely [G7]bedroom
We [F]ran out of words to say

Except the nights we’d turn away
And lie awake and cry here in the [G7]bedroom
[C]With these papers in our hands
We look [F]back where love [C]began
And wonder did we close the door to [G7]soon
[C]At two soft pillows and tangled sheets
An unmade [F]bed where no one [C]sleeps
As we take one last [G7]look at the [C]bedroom
Two soft pillows and tangled sheets
An unmade [F]bed where no one [C]sleeps
Standing here just [G7]looking at the [C]bedroom